From 5e6e697843831149acccb1aa3a3076ff640258f8 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ganesh Kariganuru Mahabalesh <gkarigan@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Mon, 21 Jul 2025 12:50:19 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] QSDK:CP:wifi:ath12k: Ensure arvif is created before updating
 splitphy bank ID

Currently, during split PHY configuration, the driver iterates over all
links in the `links_map` and updates the `splitphy_ds_bank_id` for each
associated `iter_arvif`. However, this logic does not check whether the
link has been fully created (`is_created`), which can lead to unintended
access to uninitialized or invalid link contexts.

Fix this by adding a check for `!iter_arvif->is_created` in the loop
to skip the link if it is not created yet. Once the chanctx is assigned
for that link, we will eventually iterate over that link again

Patch-dependency:
	0337-01-QSDK-DP-wifi-Add-support-for-PPE-DS-Direct-switch-fe.patch

Signed-off-by: Vignesh C <vignc@qti.qualcomm.com>
Signed-off-by: Ganesh Kariganuru Mahabalesh <gkarigan@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/ppe.c |    4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/ppe.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/ppe.c
@@ -1262,7 +1262,7 @@ static int ath12k_ppeds_attach_link_apvl
 			iter_arvif = ahvif->link[link_idx];
 
 			if (!iter_arvif || iter_arvif == arvif ||
-			    ab != iter_arvif->ar->ab)
+			    !iter_arvif->is_created || ab != iter_arvif->ar->ab)
 				continue;
 
 			iter_arvif->splitphy_ds_bank_id =
@@ -1442,7 +1442,7 @@ int ath12k_ppeds_attach_link_vif(struct
 			iter_arvif = ahvif->link[link_idx];
 
 			if (!iter_arvif || iter_arvif == arvif ||
-			    !iter_arvif->ar || ab != iter_arvif->ar->ab)
+			    !iter_arvif->is_created || ab != iter_arvif->ar->ab)
 				continue;
 
 			iter_arvif->splitphy_ds_bank_id = arvif->splitphy_ds_bank_id;
